defs.docs: This crate provides basic interfaces and data structures for building RDF parsers.

defs.name: iri
defs.docs: Utilities to validate and resolve IRIs following [RFC 3987](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3987).

defs.name: parse
defs.docs: Parses and validates the IRI following [RFC 3987](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3987) IRI syntax.

defs.name: resolve
defs.docs:
Validates and resolved a relative IRI against the current IRI
 following [RFC 3986](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3986) relative URI resolution algorithm.

defs.name: resolve_into
defs.value: fn (&self, iri: &str, target_buffer: &mut String) -> Result<(), IriParseError>
defs.docs:
Validates and resolved a relative IRI against the current IRI
 following [RFC 3986](https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3986) relative URI resolution algorithm.

defs.name: model
defs.docs: Data structures for [RDF 1.1 Concepts](https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf11-concepts/) like IRI, literal or triples.

defs.name: Simple
defs.docs: A [simple literal](https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf11-concepts/#dfn-simple-literal) without datatype or language form.

defs.name: Typed
defs.docs: A literal with an explicit datatype

defs.name: parse_all
defs.value: fn <E> (&mut self, on_triple: &mut impl FnMut(Triple) -> Result<(), E>) -> Result<(), E>
defs.docs: Parses the complete file and calls `on_triple` each time a new triple is read.

defs.name: parse_step
defs.value: fn <E> (&mut self, on_triple: &mut impl FnMut(Triple) -> Result<(), E>) -> Result<(), E>
defs.docs:
Parses a small chunk of the file and calls `on_triple` each time a new triple is read.
 (A "small chunk" could be a line for an N-Triples parser.)

defs.name: is_end
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the file has been completely consumed by the parser.

defs.name: into_iter
defs.value: fn <T, E, F> (self, convert_triple: F) -> TriplesParserIterator<T, E, F, Self>
defs.docs: Converts the parser into a `Result<T, E>` iterator.

defs.name: parse_all
defs.value: fn <E> (&mut self, on_quad: &mut impl FnMut(Quad) -> Result<(), E>) -> Result<(), E>
defs.docs: Parses the complete file and calls `on_quad` each time a new quad is read.

defs.name: parse_step
defs.value: fn <E> (&mut self, on_quad: &mut impl FnMut(Quad) -> Result<(), E>) -> Result<(), E>
defs.docs:
Parses a small chunk of the file and calls `on_quad` each time a new quad is read.
 (A "small chunk" could be a line for an N-Quads parser.)

defs.name: is_end
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the file has been completely consumed by the parser.

defs.name: into_iter
defs.value: fn <T, E, F> (self, convert_quad: F) -> QuadsParserIterator<T, E, F, Self>
defs.docs: Converts the parser into a `Result<T, E>` iterator.

defs.name: ParseError
defs.docs: Error trait that allows to get the textual position of the error

defs.name: textual_position
defs.docs: Returns the position of the error in the text, if known.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new position where `line_number` and `byte_number` are both starting from 1

defs.name: line_number
defs.docs: The line number where the error occurred starting from 0

defs.name: byte_number
defs.docs: The byte number where the error occurred starting from 0
